title.narrative: Safe Cities Free From Violence Against Women And Girls

description.narrative: (Egypt): Through the Safe Cities Free From Violence Against Women and Girls activity, USAID/EGYPT is supporting the Government of Egypt (GOE) to sustain economic growth, ensure national stability, and achieve self-reliance by combating violence against women. The widespread presence of violence against women across Egyptian society and the weak capacity of national and local institutions to assist victims perpetuates the cycle of violence, discrimination, and criminal activity. Moreover, the culture of violence and harassment discourages women from fully integrating into the economy and society. The Safe Cities Free From Violence Against Women and Girls Activity supports the GOE in their efforts to modernize Egypt's legal and policy framework protecting victims of violence. USAID/EGYPT is working with the GOE to increase the technical capacity of first responders, enhance community-based services for rehabilitation, health, and legal support for victims, while increasing public outreach activities to increase awareness and reduce social acceptance of such crimes. .. .
